			Profile
			
			&nbsp;






TingzhongYang,MD,Professor/Director,CenterforTobaccoControlResearchatZhejiangUniversity,SchoolofMedicine.Dr.YanggraduatedfromDepartmentofPublicHealthofShanxiMedicineUniversityin1982.HewasappraisedasanoutstandingcontributingscientistbythegovernmentofJiangsuprovincein1994,andservedattheUniversityofCalifornia,SanDiego,asAssistantResearchScientistfrom1998to2000.Dr.YangisamemberofthestandingandexpertgroupofNationalAssociationonTobaccoControl.HealsoisanexternalfacultyaffiliateofInjuryControlResearch,WestVirginalUniversity,U.S.HewasapastadvisorfortheWorldHealthOrganization(WHO)indeliveringpolicyandprogramontobaccocontroltohealthprofessionsstudents,andamemberoftheexecutivesandexpertgroupofNationalAssociationonTobaccoControl.Hisprimaryacademicfocusishealthbehavior,andresearchinterestsareintobaccocontroladvocacyandmentalstress.DrYangrecentlyconductedresearchastheprincipalinvestigatorofanumberofprojects.The&ldquo;tobaccocontroladvocacycapacity&rdquo;projectscoveredallprovinces,municipalitiesandautonomousregionsinwholenation,includingmorethan70cities.Hehaspublishedmorethan140papers.PapersfromclinicaldisciplineswrittenbyChineseauthorshavebeenrecognizedasbeing&nbsp;citedonhighfrequencyin2008(ChinaInstituteofScientificandTechnicalInformation).Inrecentyearshepublishedmorethan30Englishpapers,andseveralpaperswerecitedbyWHOreportontheglobaltobaccoepidemic,andotherofficialdocuments.HeservesasAsianEditorforAmericanJournalofHealthBehavior,EditorialBoardMemberforJournalofBiosafety&amp;HealthEducationandAddictionMedicine&nbsp;&amp;Therapy,andapeerreviewerformorethan20journals,includingTobaccoControl,Nicotine&amp;TobaccoResearch,HealthandPlace,SocialPsychiatryandPsychiatricEpidemiology,etc.
